Taiwan Equity Movers Column: Acer Inc., EVA Airways, HTC Corp.

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-08T06:52:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/eva-airways-htc-taiwan-semiconductor-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 19.36 points, or 0.3 percent, to
7,548.37.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) jumped 7 percent to NT$35.25 after
Macquarie Group Ltd. removed the company from its “sell list.”
The brokerage said the stock has “substantially
underperformed” the Taiwan market and the management is making
structural changes to turn the company around.  EVA Airways Corp. (2618)  (2618 TT) retreated 2.5 percent to
NT$19.80. Taiwan’s second-largest carrier said August sales fell
4.6 percent to NT$9.4 billion ($323 million) from a year
earlier, according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) increased 3.4 percent to NT$783, the
highest close since Aug. 17.  Asia ’s second-biggest maker of
smartphones filed infringement claims against Apple Inc.
yesterday, using patents it bought from Google Inc. last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  